'''Waterfiends''' can be found in the [[Ancient Cavern]] underneath the [[Baxtorian Falls]], [[Kraken Cove]] and [[Iorwerth Dungeon]]. They are moderately resistant to all forms of combat with the exception of crush attacks, which they are significantly more vulnerable against. They use a magic attack whose projectile resembles [[Water Blast]], along with a [[magical ranged]] attack resembling [[ice arrows]].

[[Duradel]] and [[Konar quo Maten]] are the only Slayer masters who assign waterfiends, and are a rare assignment. To unlock waterfiends as a task, players must have at least level 75 [[combat]] (unless they have requested Slayer masters ignore combat level requirements), and have progressed [[Barbarian training]] up to being prompted to access to the [[Ancient cavern]] as part of Barbarian Firemaking training.{{CiteTwitter|author=Mod Ash|url=https://twitter.com/JagexAsh/status/1290053229087043590|date=3 August 2020|archiveurl=https://archive.is/cdKNx|archivedate=3 August 2020|quote=Ah. It's the bit where you're being told about pyre ships, and Otto tells you to go jump in the whirlpool to get bones for them.}}

Killing a waterfiend is a requirement for an [[Clue scroll (elite)|elite clue scroll]].

